{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eea4a3ef-a5d8-468c-801c-656674a3f8ae","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates one instance **per HTTP request** — each request is a natural scope boundary. In MAUI, there's no equivalent request lifecycle. The app has a single long-lived scope, so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton`. Your DbContext (and its change tracker) lives for the entire app session.\n\n**Fixes:**\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient<MyDbContext>()`** — new instance per injection (simplest fix).\n\n2. **Create scopes manually** using `IServiceScopeFactory`:\n   ```csharp\n   using var scope = scopeFactory.CreateScope();\n   var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n\n3. **Use a DbContext factory** (recommended for MAUI):\n   ```csharp\n   builder.Services.AddDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>(opts => ...);\n   ```\n   Then inject `IDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>` and call `CreateDbContext()` when needed, disposing it yourself.\n\nOption 3 gives you explicit lifetime control, which aligns best with MAUI's navigation model.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5a9fa714-09d9-4bd6-8c3c-4f9cff5236cf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common pitfall when migrating from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scoping. This is a conceptual question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.\n\nThe key issue: In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance per HTTP request (each request is a \"scope\"). In MAUI, there's no equivalent of an HTTP request to define scope boundaries. MAUI apps typically have a single long-lived scope (the app's lifetime), so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton` — the same DbContext instance lives for the entire app session.\n\n\nThis means data appears to persist across page navigations because the same DbContext and its change tracker are reused throughout the app's lifetime.","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"5024:354872:1D1D067:203D0D8:69FA923D"},"id":"5e37ce1a-3721-4a23-a458-e6b7af787194","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:58:47.628Z","parentId":"79407213-a85a-475e-ade8-c237208b0356"}
